<item>
            <title>[FLINK-20158] KafkaSource does not implement ResultTypeQueryable</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/FLINK-20158</link>
                <project id="12315522" key="FLINK">Flink</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;As a user of the new Kafka Source introduced in (&lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/FLINK-18323&quot; title=&quot;Implement a Kafka Source based on new Source API&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;FLINK-18323&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;FLINK-18323&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;), I always have to specify the return type:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;div class=&quot;code panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;codeContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre class=&quot;code-java&quot;&gt;
DataStream&amp;lt;Event&amp;gt; events = env.fromSource(source, WatermarkStrategy.noWatermarks(),
			&lt;span class=&quot;code-quote&quot;&gt;&quot;Kafka Source&quot;&lt;/span&gt;).returns(TypeInformation.of(Event.class));
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The old Kafka source implementation implements &lt;tt&gt;ResultTypeQueryable&lt;/tt&gt;, which allows the DataStream API to get the return type from the deserializer.&lt;br/&gt;
The new Kafka Source also should have access to the produced type from the deserializer to forward it.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
